<br>
Yes, there should be a rule prohibiting this kind of post.<br>
<br>
No, there should not be a rule.<br>
<br>
I don't like overly specific legislation.  It makes me nervous.  Therefore, I would vote no for this idea, NOT because I like posting private information in public places.  I would vote no because I have a greater fear of drowning in an excess of trivial rules.<br>
<br>
Regarding the specific subject, I will say:  Those who receive private material are normally ethically bound to keep it private.  However, no matter what you call the electronic forum, be it &quot;email&quot;, &quot;my special web pictures,&quot; or &quot;Sekrit Guild Forum -- All Others Keep OuT,&quot; it is nominally public and you should be ready to defend and take responsibility for every word that you type.<br>
<br>
I think there are a lot of folks out there who don't fully understand that words spoken in confidence are not the same as private thoughts.<br>
<br>
